  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666966360418-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666966360418-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666966360418-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666966360418-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666966360418-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>to a chopping board</p><p>Slice through the thickest part of the chicken breast portions, being careful not to cut all the way through, then open them out like a book</p><p>Cover them with<strong> cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until they are of even thickness – this is your <strong>butterflied chicken</strong></p><p>Crush the <strong>crispy onions</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> in their bag<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and add them to a plate</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666966371694-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666966371694-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666966371694-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666966371694-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666966371694-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Evenly coat both sides of the <strong>butterflied chicken</strong> in the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> using the back of a spoon (not a mustard fan? Go easy!)</p><p>Add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>to the plate of <strong>crispy onions</strong> – this is your <strong>mustard & onion chicken</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>mustard & onion chicken </strong>to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and set aside</p><p>Peel and slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666966383662-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666966383662-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666966383662-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666966383662-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666966383662-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in half</p><p>Once softened, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>to the pan and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1666966388534-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
